+# ADR 0006 — Stabilization: home-route link uses next/link, add a navigation guard test
+
+Status: Accepted
+Date: 2026-05-28
+Seed: sdlc2/ai-bookkeeper-cert-3
+Supersedes/relates: stabilization debt carried by cert-1 (shipped via scope-creep) and cert-2 (held formatMoney's release on it)
+
+## Context
+The stabilization seed reports a Next.js lint regression in `src/app/page.tsx`: a raw
+`<a href="/">` element flagged by `@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages`, blocking release for two cycles.
+
+Empirical finding (inspected the committed tree, not the seed's description):
+- `src/app/page.tsx:12` — the home/brand link is ALREADY `<Link href="/">` (next/link). `next/link` is imported (`page.tsx:2`).
+- Every internal page route on the page already uses `<Link>`: `/` (l.12), `/pricing` (l.35,119,366,429), `/faq` (l.38,435), `/dashboard` (l.41,409,441).
+- The only raw `<a>` tags target in-page hash anchors (`#how`, `#start` — l.31,45,106,401), which `no-html-link-for-pages` does NOT flag.
+- `eslint .` exits 0 (GREEN). The functional `<a>`→`<Link>` conversion the seed asks for is already present — it is a no-op.
+
+So the trunk is already lint-green; the risk is regression recurrence, not an open defect. The debt that churned cert-1/cert-2 has no behavioral guard locking it in.
+
+## Decision
+Do NOT modify `src/app/page.tsx` — the `<Link href="/">` fix is already in place; touching it would be unjustified churn.
+Lock in the fix with the minimal increment the seed explicitly requested: ONE focused Playwright e2e test asserting the home/brand link performs client-side Next navigation back to `/`. Lint (`eslint .`) remains the structural guard for `no-html-link-for-pages` and is already in the quality gate.
+
+Considered and rejected:
+- React-render unit test of `page.tsx`: testing-library/jsdom are NOT installed; adding them is scope creep, forbidden this run.
+- Editing `page.tsx` to "convert `<a>`": no raw page-link `<a>` exists; nothing to convert.
+
+## Consequences
+- Trunk stays GREEN; a behavioral regression guard now exists so the debt cannot silently return.
+- New file only: `e2e/home-nav.spec.ts`. `src/app/page.tsx` is untouched.
+- Non-functional change → PATCH release. NOTE: current version is `0.4.0`, so the PATCH is `0.4.1`. The seed's "0.5.x" does not match the actual version (0.5.0 would be a MINOR). Versioning is the Release Manager's call — flagged for resolution.
+
+### Out of scope this run (do NOT bundle)
+- ADR 0005 money-formatting consolidation (separate, already drafted as docs/adr/0005).
+- Converting hash-anchor `<a>` (`#how`/`#start`) to buttons or smooth-scroll handlers.
+- Any visual refresh, copy change, or component refactor on the landing page.
+- Adding a component-test harness (testing-library) — defer until a real consumer needs it.
+
